---
/**
 * Financial Disclosure Full — complete disclosure page with 9 sections.
 */

import SectionShell from "../ui/SectionShell.astro";
import site from "../../content/site.json";
import strings from "../../content/strings/en.json";
---

<SectionShell
  eyebrow="Legal and financials"
  title="Financial Disclosures"
  body="TEMPLATE: Version date. List what this page covers: filings, ratios, audits, funding sources, governance, registry info, and contacts."
>
  <div class="legal-index" aria-label={strings.accessibility.otherLegalPages}>
    <a href="/privacy">{strings.footer.privacyPolicy}</a>
    <a href="/terms">{strings.footer.termsOfUse}</a>
    <a href="/accessibility">{strings.footer.accessibility}</a>
    <a href="/non-discrimination">{strings.footer.nonDiscrimination}</a>
    <a href="/financials#donor-rights">{strings.footer.donorBillOfRights}</a>
  </div>
  <div class="disclosure-nav">
    <a href="#tax-status">01 Tax-exempt status</a>
    <a href="#form-990">02 Form 990 filings</a>
    <a href="#audited-financials">03 Audited financials</a>
    <a href="#major-funders">04 Major funders</a>
    <a href="#financial-ratios">05 Financial ratios</a>
    <a href="#executive-compensation">06 Executive compensation</a>
    <a href="#governance-policies">07 Governance policies</a>
    <a href="#state-registry">08 State charitable registry</a>
    <a href="#financial-contact">09 Contact</a>
  </div>
  <div class="grid two">
    <div class="card disclosure-section" id="tax-status">
      <h3>01. Tax-exempt status</h3>
      <p>TEMPLATE: Org name is a tax-exempt charitable organization under Section 501(c)(3). Contributions are tax-deductible to the extent provided by law.</p>
      <ul class="proof-list">
        <li><strong>EIN:</strong> {site.ein}</li>
        <li><strong>TEMPLATE: State entity number</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Fiscal year:</strong> TEMPLATE: Start to end</li>
        <li><strong>Founded:</strong> {site.foundedYear}</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card disclosure-section" id="form-990">
      <h3>02. Form 990 filings</h3>
      <p>TEMPLATE: Org name publishes IRS Form 990 annually. Recent filings should be available through ProPublica Nonprofit Explorer and Candid.</p>
      <table class="mini-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Filing</th><th>Download</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>TEMPLATE: Most recent fiscal year</td><td><span class="tag">View on ProPublica</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>TEMPLATE: Prior fiscal year</td><td><span class="tag">View on ProPublica</span></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="card disclosure-section" id="audited-financials">
      <h3>03. Audited financials</h3>
      <p>TEMPLATE: Describe your audit process, publication timeline, and retention period.</p>
      <p><strong>Current document:</strong> TEMPLATE: Most recent audited statement title.</p>
      <p>For prior years or additional requests, contact {site.email}.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card disclosure-section" id="major-funders">
      <h3>04. Major funders</h3>
      <p>TEMPLATE: List major public and private funding sources. Reconcile against current grant records before each annual update.</p>
      <ul class="proof-list">
        <li>TEMPLATE: Funder 1</li>
        <li>TEMPLATE: Funder 2</li>
        <li>TEMPLATE: Funder 3</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card disclosure-section" id="financial-ratios">
      <h3>05. Financial ratios</h3>
      <p>TEMPLATE: Program expense ratio from audited figures. Full functional expense breakdown is in Form 990 and audited financial statements.</p>
      <ul class="proof-list">
        <li><strong>TEMPLATE: Rating agency 1</strong></li>
        <li><strong>TEMPLATE: Rating agency 2</strong></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card disclosure-section" id="executive-compensation">
      <h3>06. Executive compensation</h3>
      <p>Compensation for the Chief Executive Officer and other key staff is disclosed in IRS Form 990, Part VII and Schedule J. CEO compensation is reviewed annually by the Board of Directors.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card disclosure-section" id="governance-policies">
      <h3>07. Governance policies</h3>
      <p>TEMPLATE: Org name maintains governance policies available to the public on request.</p>
      <ul class="proof-list">
        <li>Conflict-of-Interest Policy</li>
        <li>Whistleblower Protection Policy</li>
        <li>Document Retention and Destruction Policy</li>
        <li>Joint-Cost Allocation Policy</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card disclosure-section" id="state-registry">
      <h3>08. State charitable registry</h3>
      <p>TEMPLATE: Describe your state charitable registration and where annual reports can be found.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="trust-note disclosure-section" id="financial-contact">
    <strong>09. Contact:</strong> Financial questions and document requests can be sent to {site.email}. TEMPLATE: Last reviewed date. This page is a plain-English summary, not a contract or substitute for legal advice.
  </div>
</SectionShell>
